---
import T7Layout from '../layouts/T7Layout.astro';
import { breadcrumbSchema } from '../lib/schema';

const title = 'Privacy Policy';
const description =
  'How UK Mortgages Worldwide collects, uses, and protects your personal information when you submit an enquiry through this site.';

const schemas = [
  breadcrumbSchema([
    { name: 'Home', path: '/' },
    { name: 'Privacy Policy' },
  ]),
];
---

<T7Layout title={title} description={description} h1="Privacy Policy" schemas={schemas}>
  <div class="t7-banner">
    <strong>This is a pre-launch draft.</strong> The final policy will be reviewed and approved by a compliance consultant before the site goes live.
  </div>

  <p class="t7-meta">Last updated: [DATE]</p>

  <hr class="t7-divider" />

  <h2>Who we are</h2>
  <p>UK Mortgages Worldwide is operated by [ENTITY NAME TBD], a company registered in England and Wales. Our registered office is at [REGISTERED ADDRESS TBD].</p>
  <p>For the purposes of UK data protection law (the UK General Data Protection Regulation and the Data Protection Act 2018), we are the data controller of any personal information you provide to us through this website.</p>
  <p>If you have any questions about this policy or our handling of your personal data, please contact us at enquiry@ukmortgagesworldwide.com.</p>

  <h2>What this policy covers</h2>
  <p>This policy explains:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>What personal information we collect about you</li>
    <li>How we collect that information</li>
    <li>Why we collect it and what we do with it</li>
    <li>How long we keep it</li>
    <li>Who we share it with</li>
    <li>Your rights in relation to your personal information</li>
    <li>How we keep your information secure</li>
    <li>How to contact us</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Information we collect</h2>
  <p>We collect personal information in two ways: information you give us directly, and information collected automatically when you use the site.</p>

  <h3>Information you provide directly</h3>
  <p>When you submit an enquiry through our contact form, we collect:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Your first name</li>
    <li>Your contact telephone number or WhatsApp number</li>
    <li>Your email address</li>
    <li>Your country of residence</li>
    <li>Any additional information you choose to share in the message field</li>
  </ul>
  <p>You provide this information voluntarily when you choose to submit an enquiry.</p>

  <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
  <p>When you visit the site, we automatically collect limited technical information through standard server logs and analytics tools. This may include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Your IP address</li>
    <li>The type of device, browser, and operating system you use</li>
    <li>The pages you view and the time you spend on each</li>
    <li>The site or source that referred you to our site</li>
    <li>The general geographic location associated with your IP address (country and region, not precise location)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>This information is collected through cookies and similar technologies. See our Cookies Policy for details.</p>

  <h2>Why we collect your information</h2>
  <p>We use the information you provide to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Respond to your enquiry and pass it to a suitable FCA-authorised mortgage broker for the regulated conversation</li>
    <li>Communicate with you about your enquiry, including any follow-up questions</li>
    <li>Maintain a record of enquiries received for our own business purposes</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We use the technical information we collect automatically to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Operate, secure, and maintain the site</li>
    <li>Understand how visitors use the site so we can improve it</li>
    <li>Detect and prevent fraud or misuse</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Lawful basis for processing your information</h2>
  <p>Under UK data protection law, we must have a lawful basis to process your personal information. Our lawful bases are:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Consent</strong>, where you have given us permission to use your information for a specific purpose. You can withdraw consent at any time.</li>
    <li><strong>Legitimate interests</strong>, where we have a genuine interest in processing your data and our interests do not override your rights. This applies to our use of technical site analytics.</li>
    <li><strong>Legal obligation</strong>, where we are required to retain or process information to comply with the law.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>When you submit an enquiry, your consent is the lawful basis for sharing your details with the broker who will contact you.</p>

  <h2>Who we share your information with</h2>
  <p>We share the personal information you provide in your enquiry with the FCA-authorised mortgage broker we introduce you to. The broker will use your information to contact you about your mortgage enquiry, and any further use is governed by the broker's own privacy policy, which they will share with you when they make contact.</p>
  <p>We may also share your information with:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Service providers who help us operate the site (for example, hosting providers, form submission services). These providers act under contract and process your information only on our instructions.</li>
    <li>Legal or regulatory authorities, where we are required to do so by law.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We do not sell your personal information to anyone.</p>
  <p>We do not share your information with marketing companies or advertising networks.</p>

  <h2>International transfers</h2>
  <p>Some of the service providers we use (for example, hosting infrastructure) may store or process your information outside the UK. Where this happens, we ensure the transfer is protected by appropriate safeguards as required by UK data protection law, such as standard contractual clauses or transfers to countries deemed adequate by the UK government.</p>

  <h2>How long we keep your information</h2>
  <p>We keep your enquiry information for as long as is necessary to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Respond to your enquiry and complete the introduction</li>
    <li>Comply with any legal, regulatory, or accounting requirements</li>
    <li>Resolve disputes or enforce our rights</li>
  </ul>
  <p>In practice, this means we typically retain enquiry data for up to six years from the date of the enquiry. After this period we will delete or anonymise the information.</p>
  <p>Technical site data collected through analytics is typically retained for shorter periods, as set by the analytics provider.</p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>Under UK data protection law, you have the following rights in relation to your personal information:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>The right to be informed</strong> about how we use your data (which this policy covers).</li>
    <li><strong>The right of access</strong> to a copy of the personal information we hold about you.</li>
    <li><strong>The right to rectification</strong> of inaccurate or incomplete information.</li>
    <li><strong>The right to erasure</strong> of your information in certain circumstances ("the right to be forgotten").</li>
    <li><strong>The right to restrict processing</strong> of your information in certain circumstances.</li>
    <li><strong>The right to data portability</strong>, allowing you to obtain and reuse your information.</li>
    <li><strong>The right to object</strong> to certain types of processing, including direct marketing.</li>
    <li><strong>The right to withdraw consent</strong> at any time, where we rely on consent as our lawful basis.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>To exercise any of these rights, contact us at enquiry@ukmortgagesworldwide.com.</p>
  <p>You also have the right to complain to the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) if you are unhappy with how we handle your personal information. The ICO can be contacted at ico.org.uk or by telephone on 0303 123 1113.</p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>We take appropriate technical and organisational measures to protect your personal information against unauthorised access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. These measures include encrypted connections to the site (HTTPS), restricted access to enquiry data, and the use of reputable service providers.</p>
  <p>No method of transmission over the internet is completely secure. While we use reasonable measures to protect your information, we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>This site is not directed at children. We do not knowingly collect personal information from anyone under the age of 18. If you believe a child has submitted information to us, please contact us and we will delete it.</p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this policy from time to time. The "last updated" date at the top of the policy will reflect any changes. Material changes will be highlighted on the site for a reasonable period after they take effect.</p>

  <h2>Contact us</h2>
  <p>If you have any questions about this policy, want to exercise your rights, or want to raise a concern about how we handle your information, please contact us:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Email: enquiry@ukmortgagesworldwide.com</li>
    <li>Post: [ENTITY NAME TBD], [REGISTERED ADDRESS TBD]</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="t7-divider" />

  <div class="t7-prelaunch-note">
    <strong>Pre-launch note:</strong> This draft will be reviewed and finalised by a compliance consultant before launch. Specific entity details, registered office address, and any sector-specific provisions (FCA introducer requirements) will be added at that point.
  </div>
</T7Layout>
